		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>In group I like to manually twist my four songs.&nbsp;&nbsp;This way I can quickly switch songs if needed, as well as deal with missed notes.  But when chant kiting, whether I am just finishing off a swarm kited mob or having chant kited the whole kill, I have some custom hotkeys set up.  I put my 4 DoT songs in the top 4 spell slots.  I then make 2 hotkeys:<br><br>Hotkey 1<br><br>/stop song<br>/cast 1<br>/pause 27 (equals 2.7 seconds, or whatever cast duration of song is, 30 for 3 seconds 29 for 2.9 etc.)<br>/stop song<br>/cast 2<br><br>Hotkey 2<br><br>/stop song<br>/cast 3<br>/pause 27<br>/stop song<br>/cast 4<br><br>Then I usually key these 2 hotkeys to my + and - keys on my number pad and alternately cycle them.  This way I can chant kite without getting carpal tunnel.  Yes missed notes do happen, but I just continue on, they still die.<br><br>Yzuki 61 Bard Stromm<br><br>&quot;....and one time at Bard camp, I put my Troubador's Mace up my ass&quot;<br><br><i><span class=sm>Edited, Fri Jul 23 01:50:36 2004 by harjared</span class=sm></i></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=4><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=4&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=96656681729149&num=3&page=&post=1&mid=96656681729149><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread<